{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Battery Status API","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.BatteryManager","api.Navigator.getBattery"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\" aria-current=\"page\">Battery Status API</a></em></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery\"><code>Navigator.getBattery()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"DefaultAPISidebar","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong>Battery Status API</strong>, more often referred to as the <strong>Battery API</strong>, provides information about the system's battery charge level and lets you be notified by events that are sent when the battery level or charging status change. This can be used to adjust your app's resource usage to reduce battery drain when the battery is low, or to save changes before the battery runs out in order to prevent data loss.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This API is <em>not available</em> in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\">Web Workers</a> (not exposed via <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator\"><code>WorkerNavigator</code></a>).</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces","title":"Interfaces","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"batterymanager\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Provides information about the system's battery charge level.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"extensions_to_other_interfaces","title":"Extensions to other interfaces","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"navigator.getbattery\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery\"><code>Navigator.getBattery()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>In this example, we watch for changes both to the charging status (whether or not we're plugged in and charging) and for changes to the battery level and timing. This is done by listening for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/chargingchange_event\" title=\"chargingchange\"><code>chargingchange</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/levelchange_event\" title=\"levelchange\"><code>levelchange</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/chargingtimechange_event\" title=\"chargingtimechange\"><code>chargingtimechange</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/dischargingtimechange_event\" title=\"dischargingtimechange\"><code>dischargingtimechange</code></a> events.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getBattery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">battery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">updateAllBatteryInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateChargeInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateLevelInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateChargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateDischargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">updateAllBatteryInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"chargingchange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateChargeInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">updateChargeInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Battery charging? </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>charging <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Yes\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"No\"</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"levelchange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateLevelInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">updateLevelInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Battery level: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>level <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">%</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"chargingtimechange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateChargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">updateChargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Battery charging time: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>chargingTime<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> seconds</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"dischargingtimechange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">updateDischargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">updateDischargingInfo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Battery discharging time: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>dischargingTime<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> seconds</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>See also <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/battery-status/#examples\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">the example in the specification</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/battery/","title":"Battery Status API"}],"query":"api.BatteryManager,api.Navigator.getBattery"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"browser_compatibility","title":"Browser compatibility","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"api.BatteryManager","id":"api.BatteryManager","isH3":true,"query":"api.BatteryManager"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"api.Navigator.getBattery","id":"api.Navigator.getBattery","isH3":true,"query":"api.Navigator.getBattery"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://hacks.mozilla.org/2012/02/using-the-battery-api-part-of-webapi/\" class=\"external\" target=\"_blank\">Hacks blog post - Using the Battery API</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Interfaces","id":"interfaces"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Battery Status API, more often referred to as the Battery API, provides information about the system's battery charge level and lets you be notified by events that are sent when the battery level or charging status change. This can be used to adjust your app's resource usage to reduce battery drain when the battery is low, or to save changes before the battery runs out in order to prevent data loss.","popularity":0.0106,"modified":"2023-12-01T14:40:27.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/battery_status_api","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/battery_status_api/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/cf05364b23bc44af37a350319a1dd47485746a9c","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"Battery Status API","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API","title":"Battery Status API"}],"pageTitle":"Battery Status API - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}